What is the average speed of a car that travels `d` kilometers in `t` hours? Answer in kilometers per hour.

Light travels at approximately 3.00×108 meters per second. How long, in minutes, will it take to travel `d`×108 kilometers?

Hint: the answer is between 10 and 20 minutes.

item.title: Average speed of a two leged trip

material.mattext: A car has an average speed of `a` kilometers per hour for one hour, and then an average speed of `b` kilometers per hour for two hours during a three-hour trip. What was the average speed, in kilometers per hour, for the three-hour trip?
What is the average acceleration, in meters per square second, of a car that moves from `a` meters per second to `b` meters per second in `t` seconds?
Which statement about planetary motion is incorrect?
Planets that are twice as far from the sun will also have twice as long of a period of orbit.
Gravity is the force responsible for keeping planets in orbit.
Planetary orbits are elliptical.
The sun is at a focal point of the planet's orbit.
If the distance between a planet and its star were to double, the force of gravity between them would only be a quarter of the strength.
In our solar system, planetary orbits are nearly circular.
Six objects are moving on the x-axis, and their positions are plotted over time in the figure below. Which statement is incorrect about their motion.
Object 3 (thin cyan dashed line) has a velocity that is negative from 0 to 6.3 seconds.
Object 6 (solid green line) is not moving.
Object 5 (thick purple dashed line) has negative acceleration.
Object 4 (thin yellow narrow dotted line) has uniform motion.
At the 5 second mark, Object 1 (thin blue solid line) is at 2 meters.
The velocity of Object 2 (thick red solid line) increases over time.

What is the centripetal acceleration, in m/s2, of a object spinning in a uniform circle of diameter `d` meters, and is spinning at `v` meters per second?
